        },
        "committer": {
          "name": "Fan Yong",
          "email": "yong.fan@whamcloud.com",
          "date": "2012-04-08 06:47:45.000000000",
          "tz": 480
        },
        "subject": "LU-957 scrub: general framework for new LFSCK",
        "message": "LU-957 scrub: general framework for new LFSCK\n\nLFSCK contains several components, different components may\nperform checking/repairing in different layers. This patch\ndefines common iterfaces and functions, which can be shared\namong these different components.\n\n1) Scrub head\nFor each level (layer), there is a single scrub head, for the\nversions, common parameters, and etc.\n\n2) Scrub unit\nFor each LFSCK component, there is a scrub unit, to trace its\nprocessing: how many objects have been checked/updated/failed,\nthe latest position, the first failure position, and so on.\n\n3) Checkpoint file\nFor each level (layer), there is a single checkpoint file to\nrecord both the scrub head and the scrub units in the level.\nThe checkpoint file is only visible inside its level.\n\n4) scrub_prep()\nEach LFSCK component can register an prep() function to prepare\nsomething before related LFSCK component start.\n\n5) scrub_exec()\nEach LFSCK component must register an exec() function to perform\ncorresponding system component checking/repairing.\n\n6) scrub_post()\nEach LFSCK component can register an post() function to cleanup\nsomething before related LFSCK component stop.\n\nSigned-off-by: Fan Yong <yong.fan@whamcloud.com>\nChange-Id: Idea5446d8790b96c9e7a6f44f9c1ed07b15e5470\n"
      },
      "branch": "refs/heads/master"
    }
  },
